President Muhammadu Buhari on Friday left Abuja to his hometown, Daura, Katsina State in order to participate in the All Progressives Congress (APC) ward congress slated for Saturday. The presidential jet conveying him from Abuja touched down at Umaru Musa Ya’Adua Airport, Katsina around 4:30 pm. He was immediately conveyed in a police chopper to Daura. Buhari had returned to Nigeria on Thursday night from his official visit to the United States. Before arriving in Nigeria, Buhari had a ‘technical stop-over,’ in London, United Kingdom.